Anonymous Thu 23 Jul 2020 15:19:55 No.31664424 Report
Quoted By:
>>31664218
Good question.

The fur's broadly fall into two categories.

The ones who were artificially made and were delivered as adults (Dr. Hopper, Marilyn, Charlotte's Mom). Basically their aging process was accelerated so those years are gone. So Hopper is chronologically only in her early 40's, but is physically in her late 50's.

Born fur's age and mature much like humans do, and are likely to have a similar lifespan. But there's the issue of medical complications, I would imagine the huge variety of fur's would have a huge variety of unique and unheard of medical problems, so average age might be brought down as a result of that. You could argue Charlotte's mom died of such a condition. There's also the possibility that scaly and avian furs might have extended lifespan owing to their borrowed DNA.

But a lot of these are unanswered questions, simply because even the oldest furs are only as old as Dr. Hopper. They don't have good data on the fur life-cycle and I'm sure the fur government is just as concerned about a potential population collapse in 10-20 years if it turns out their lifespans are not comparable to humans.
